    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hi, i'm in the middle of buying my first house in austin and i'm a bit confused. my realtor mentioned my earnest money is being held in an escrow account. can u explain what that actually means and why they don't just give it to the seller right away?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Earnest money is a deposit you put down to show the seller you are serious about the purchase. It's held in escrow, which is a neutral third-party account, to protect both you and the seller. This prevents either party from unilaterally keeping the money if the deal falls through due to a contractual issue. The funds are only released to the seller once all closing conditions are met.",
