    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay that makes sense. but what if the inspection comes back and there's like, major structural damage or something? can i get that money back? or is it stuck in there if the seller refuses to fix things?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the inspection reveals major issues, you usually have the right to negotiate repairs or renegotiate the price before moving forward. If the seller refuses to address significant, agreed-upon issues, you can often use your earnest money to back out of the contract without losing your deposit. However, this depends heavily on the specific contingencies written into your purchase agreement. It's crucial to review those contingencies carefully with your realtor.",
